metadata.name: Voyage #44
metadata.description:
Journey through barren land,
Array in glory your immortal ray;
Unnoticed like the sacred spirit of light;
And clouds of armour tune your filial aid
Almost the silence trembled and began,
Earth with the gleaming vapours of thy day;
Hold thy bright sceptre on the flowing breeze:
Loosed from the floor with keen precision.
_

Generative visual composition, hybrid techniques, animation, textures source created with GAN, assist by AI, layers transform in autonomous system, eclectic, colors, additional algorithm, glitch, modular patch, and combine with other elements that made with code.

metadata.name: Do Touch #170
metadata.description:
o History tells us an isolated system tends to evolve from order to disorder, and from this disorder beauty arises. Chaos builds over time, ultimately perishing and a new cycle emerges. In the chaos, one may want to embrace a moment and will need to intervene to preserve the dynamics.
o This project assembles the progress, with triangle grids inter-linked with each other and influenced by the environment’s forces. The movement speeds up over time, and the art piece system will run into chaos unless an interaction is made.
o This project is a cooperation between the artist and the viewer. The artist sets the art system's behavior and the viewer intervenes to express his/her preference. Do touch, do intervene.

Touch keys:
o View construction steps: press number keys 1,2,3,4 to see steps
o Static view: q to pause movement, w to resume
o Push: use arrow key up, down, left, right to push the triangles
o Comfort speed zone: press 0 to let them range bound in current speed
o Accelerate or decelerate the chaos: - to slow things down, = to increase movement
o “I am done, free them”: press f key to free the triangles to roam outside of the canvas

This project consists of Mini sets:
o Pop: bold palette
o Classic: retro palette
o Day Dream: soft n romantic palette
o Vanilla: time-lapse color background, no shades
o Sonata: black n white keys
o Paper: white background, no shades

metadata.name: Symbology437 #53
metadata.description:
Abstract, distorted compositions using symbols from the original IBM VGA codepage 437 character set. The symbols were created in code as bitmaps, scaled, and then drawn onto the canvas. The shading is based on the characters and sets from ANSI and ASCII art styles. 

There are 4 main types of outputs:
- Abstracts, 50%
- Random characters, 25%
- One of 16 preset character layouts, 25%
- One of 16 custom symbol PFP styles that will be 10% of the total outputs

For abstracts, there are several main styles created from layering different base shapes: circles, filled circles, rectangles, flow field lines, and rain-like streaks.

Color combinations include monochromatic, green or amber, dark mode, and multicolor.

Press 's' to save the image. The size is 2318x3000px, and for PFPs, the size is 3000x3000px.
